snippet: In 1993, he attended the Vrije Universiteit Brussel where he graduated in 1998 in Business Engineering. He attended Northwestern University in Evanston, Illinois, in 2002, and completed an MBA at the Kellogg School of Management in 2004.

title: VUB alumnus Alexander De Croo becomes Prime Minister of Belg | Vrije Universiteit Brussel
snippet: 493 days after the last federal elections, the political parties PS, sp.a, Groen, Ecolo, CD&V, MR and Open VLD form a Belgian government. The government will be headed by Alexander De Croo, 45 years old and alumnus of VUB, where he graduated with great distinction as a commercial engineer.
